Subject: RE: [T2] Engine temperatures

I don't have a tachometer, but my tires are stock size, transmission is
original and, as I had mentioned, I was doing 60 to 65 MPH, when I got these
readings.

I read in either the Bently book or Miur that the oil pressure relief valve
opens at 28 psi in a dual relief case, which I have.  Of course, my OP
readings with cold oil are much higher, like 55 to 60 psi.  My HIOP is about
5 psi.  With the new VDO OP sender (the one with outputs for both the gauge
and the idiot light), the oil ight comes on at hot idle, but this did not
happen with the old OP switch.  My idle may be adjusted a little too slow,
so that will get checked and fixed soon - before the next trip.  I'm using
10W40 oil, and I may switch to 15W40.

Your temperature readings make sense to me, even the oil cooler inlet being
hotter by 20 degrees, which I would expect.

I'm putting my faith in the gauges, too.

-----Original Message-----
